HEADWORD: Loaning
<hw>Loan"ing</hw>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From Scotch <ets>loan</ets>, E.
<ets>lawn</ets>.]</ety> <def>An open space between cultivated fields
through which cattle are driven, and where the cows are sometimes
milked; also, a lane.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark> <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

